{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_28","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `io.fabric8:kubernetes-model-core:7.7.0`. Preserved work is available on `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-7959-fails-javac-compile-io.fabric8-kubernetes-model-core-7.7.0-b9f8c66e`.\n\nThe original failing stage was `compileTestJava`: `logs/io.fabric8:kubernetes-model-core:7.7.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T10-37-49-947476Z.log` shows 4 compilation errors in `tests/src/io.fabric8/kubernetes-model-core/7.7.0/src/test/java/io_fabric8/kubernetes_model_core/Kubernetes_model_coreTest.java` at lines 294, 342, 695, and 733 because `ServiceListFluent`, `ConfigMapListFluent`, `EventListFluent`, and `PodListFluent` in 7.7.0 no longer accept `withNewMetadata(null, null, ..., null)` and now require the no-arg `withNewMetadata()` builder pattern. However, the preserved branch already updates those call sites, and the later reruns in `logs/io.fabric8:kubernetes-model-core:7.7.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T10-38-51-018430Z.log`, `logs/io.fabric8:kubernetes-model-core:7.7.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T10-39-49-928048Z.log`, `logs/io.fabric8:kubernetes-model-core:7.7.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T10-40-06-245929Z.log`, and `logs/io.fabric8:kubernetes-model-core:7.7.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T10-40-23-632410Z.log` all end with `8 tests successful` and `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`.\n\nThe remaining failure looks most likely to be in metrics/finalization rather than the compile fix itself: `stats/io.fabric8/kubernetes-model-core/7.7.0/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file/metadata_file: None`, and there is no `stats/io.fabric8/kubernetes-model-core/7.7.0/stats.json`, so dynamic-access coverage was never produced. Also inspect `logs/io.fabric8:kubernetes-model-core:7.7.0/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-06-06T10-38-51-009685Z.log` for the generation attempt that produced the preserved branch.\n\nNext steps:\n1. Review or cherry-pick the preserved branch change that replaces the four `withNewMetadata(null, null, ..., null)` calls with the 7.7.0-compatible no-arg metadata builder pattern.\n2. Re-run the `io.fabric8:kubernetes-model-core:7.7.0` test and stats/coverage generation so `stats/io.fabric8/kubernetes-model-core/7.7.0/stats.json` is produced.\n3. If the rerun still lands in human intervention, inspect the metrics/scratch-metrics finalization step because the stored execution metrics currently contradict the passing Gradle logs."}}
